cs.RO, cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR 

Reasoning: 
- cs.RO (Robotics): The paper focuses on mapping the ground reflectivity with laser scanners mounted on mobile robots/vehicles. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision): The proposed framework involves generating map-perspective gradients and applying de-noising operators, which are common techniques in computer vision. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The iterative algorithms used in the proposed framework involve minimizing an $\ell_1$ sparse regularized least squares formulation, which is a common optimization problem in machine learning. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The proposed framework involves automatic, data-driven computational mapping, which is a common application of artificial intelligence. 
- cs.GR (Graphics): The paper discusses map enhancement and artifact removal, which are common topics in computer graphics.
